  <para>
    The <classname>Unconditional</classname> <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-SkelModCriterion"/> is used as the
    <varname>criterion</varname> for &skel; <link
    linkend="RegisteredClass-SkeletonModifier">modification</link>
    operations.  It accepts any <link
    linkend='Section-Concepts-Skeleton-Illegality'>legal</link> change
    in the &skel;.  If more than one change is possible, the one that
    decreases the effective <link
    linkend="Section-Concepts-Skeleton-Energy">element energy</link>
    the most is accepted.
  </para>
  <para>
    The only difference between <classname>Unconditional</classname>
    and <xref linkend="RegisteredClass-AverageEnergy"/> is that
    <classname>Unconditional</classname> will accept modifications
    that <emphasis>increase</emphasis> the energy, if no better
    alternative exists. <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-AverageEnergy"/> will reject all
    modifications that increase the energy.
  </para>
  <para>
    See <xref linkend="RegisteredClass-AverageEnergy"/> for more
    details.
  </para>

